Asuras 1 — The foes and cognates of Devas;2 born out <BR>of the jaghana of Prajāpati; etymology of;3 could secure <BR>Hari's blessing by adorning him;4 opposed to Yajña;5 the <BR>Āsura hour;6 praise Śeṣa;7 abode down the earth.8 Ruled <BR>the earth for ten yugas when it went back to the Devas on <BR>a curse by Śukra after 12 wars;9 worship Barhiṣad Pitrs.10 <BR>Had three Indras — Hiraṇyakaśipu, Bali and Praḥlāda;11 lost <BR>their refulgence on the eve of Vāmana avatāra.12 represent <BR>night and darkness and full of tamas.13 Asura's killed in <BR>the wars with Devas are born as men in earth and create <BR>trouble in this world.14 1) Bhā. I. 13. 6; VII. 3. 37; XII. 9. 28; Br. II. 32. 1, 2. 6; <BR>M. 47. 12; 131. 10, 39-41.<BR> 2) Bhā. VI. 7. 18; Vā. 31. 11; Br. II. <BR>8. 5; IV. 9. 67-8.<BR> 3) Vā. 9. 4-5; Br. II. 8. 4; Vi. I. 5. 31.<BR> 4) Bhā. <BR>VII. 7. 50.<BR> 5) Ib. VIII. 1. 17.<BR> 6) Ib. X. 28. 2.<BR> 7) Ib. X. 39. 44-45.<BR> 8) Ib. XI. 24. 13.<BR> 9) Br. III. 72. 69-93; Vā. 97. 68-93.<BR> 10) M. 15. 3.<BR> 11) M. 47. 59.<BR> 12) M. 245. 1.<BR> 13) Br. II. 8. 4; Vi. I. 5. 31-4.<BR> 14) Br. <BR>III. 71. 263.<BR>

