Āśvalāyana — a son of Sahiṣṇu avatār of the Lord. <BR>Vā. 23. 213.

आश्वलायनि
Āśvalāyani — a pravara of Aṅgiras. <BR>M. 196. 13.

आश्वलायनिन्
Āśvalāyanins — Kaśyapagotrakaras. <BR>M. 199. 6.

आश्वायनि
Āśvāyani — a Pañcārṣeya (Bhārgavas). <BR>M. 195. 34.

आषाढ
Āṣāḍha(daśami) — a manvantara for śrāddha. <BR>M. 17. 7-8.

आषाढम्
Āṣāḍham — sacred to Aṅgāraka, and for performing <BR>śrāddha. <BR>Br. II. 21. 76; 24. 133; III. 18. 10; Vā. 53. 108; 66. 51; 82. 10.

