Āhukās — the people of an eastern kingdom. <BR>Br. II. 16. 52; Vā. 45. 121.

आहुकान्ध
Āhukāndha — married sister of Āhuka; father of two <BR>sons and a daughter. <BR>Vā. 96. 127; Br. III. 71. 127.

आहुकी
Āhukī — the daughter of Punarvasu and sister of Āhuka <BR>(s.v.) the queen of the king of Avanti (Āhukāndha). <BR>Bhā. IX. 24. 21; Br. III. 71. 121 and 127; M. 44. 66; Vā. 96. <BR>120, 127; Vi. IV. 14. 15.

आहृति
Āhṛti — a son of Vastu. <BR>Vā. 95. 37.

आहृत्य
Āhṛtya — an Apsaras gaṇa from Brahmā. <BR>Br. III. 7. 18.

आह्वय
Āhvaya — one of the names in the third marutgaṇa. <BR>Vā. 67. 126.

इकार
Ikāra — from the third face of the fourteen faced deva <BR>came Āditya, Yajurmaya and Yajurveda. <BR>Vā. 26. 34.

इक्षलक
Ikṣalaka — a pupil of Rathītara. <BR>Br. II. 35. 4.

इक्षु
Ikṣu (I) — a tree peculiar to Harivarṣa. <BR>Br. II. 17. 7.

इक्षु
Ikṣu (II) (Kratu) — a R. of Śākadvīpa, from the side <BR>of the Himalayas. <BR>Br. II. 19. 96; M. 122. 32; Vā. 49. 93; Vi. II. 4. 65.

इक्षु
Ikṣu (III) — one of the seven oceans; see Ikṣurasodā. <BR>Br. IV. 31. 18; M. 2. 34.

इक्षु
Ikṣu (IV) — a R. from the side of the Himālayas, in the <BR>Bhāratavarṣa. <BR>M. 114. 22; Vā. 45. 96.

इक्षु
Ikṣu (V) — a R. joining the Narmadā; very holy. A bath <BR>here makes one lord of a Devagaṇa. <BR>M. 191. 49-50.

