Ikṣudaṇḍam — sugarcane juice for śrāddha; one of the <BR>eight saubhāgyams. <BR>M. 7. 11 and 26; 15. 35; 60. 8; 85. 6.

इक्षुदा
Ikṣudā — a R. from Mahendra hills. <BR>M. 114. 31.

इक्षुमती
Ikṣumatī (I) — a R. On its banks was the hermitage of <BR>Kapila. <BR>Bhā. V. 10. 1; Vi. II. 13. 53.

इक्षुमती
Ikṣumatī (II) — a tīrtham sacred to Pitṛs. <BR>M. 22. 17.

