Ijyāvedātmaka — is Śrauta Ijyā or sacrifice being one of <BR>the eight practices of śiṣṭas. <BR>Br. II. 32. 40 and 44.

इडविड
Iḍaviḍa — son of Śataratha; married the daughter of <BR>Viśvasahasra. <BR>Br. III. 63. 180.

इडविडा
Iḍaviḍā — the daughter of Tṛṇabindu: a queen of Viśra<BR>vas, and mother of Kubera. <BR>Bhā. IV. 1. 37; 12. 9.

इडस्पति
Iḍaspati (I) — a son of Dakṣiṇā and a Tuṣita god. <BR>Bhā. IV. 1. 7-8.

इडस्पति
Iḍaspati (II) — a name of Hari; Puruṣa. <BR>Bhā. IX. 2. 35.

इडा
Iḍā (I) — see Ilā. <BR>Br. III. 60. 11; Vā. 85. 7.

इडा
Iḍā (II) — a śakti of Māruta. <BR>Br. IV. 33. 70.

