Iḍivilā — a daughter of Tṛṇabindu and wife of Pulastya, <BR>father of the sage Vaiśravas. <BR>Vā. 70. 31.

इति
Iti naḥ Śrutam (Iti śruti) — recording of tradition by <BR>the Purāṇas1 — also Ityevam anuśuśruma.2 Iti naḥ śrutiḥ;3 <BR>Iti śrutam;4 Iti śrutaḥ;5 Iti śruti;6 Iti hi naḥ śrutam.7 1) Br. II. 13. 27, 82; M. 3. 45; 6. 7; 24. 64; 35. 5; 36. 2; 44. 2; <BR>47. 186; 50. 4 and 7; 247. 1 and 39; Vā. 30. 25, 175 and 302; 88. <BR>153; 90. 3, 10, and 24; 95. 2; 99. 175; Vi. I. 15. 140.<BR> 2) M. 43. 19.<BR> 3) Vā. 99. 200.<BR> 4) Vā. 94. 51.<BR> 5) Ib. 88. 118, 206.<BR> 6) Vā. 21. 73; 30. 96, <BR>303; 53. 108; 59. 70; 88. 28, 182; 89. 8; 92. 70; 94. 4; 99. 231.<BR> 7) Br. I. 2. 15; Vā. 2. 15.<BR>

