Idhmajihva — a son of Priyavrata and Barhiṣmatī. <BR>Appointed lord of Plakṣadvīpa, which he divided into seven <BR>parts among his seven sons, and retired to practise auste<BR>rities. <BR>Bhā. V. 1. 25 and 33; 20. 2.

