इन्द्र
Indra (II) — the temple of, in Vidarbhā (see Indrāṇī). <BR>Bhā. X. 53. 49[1].

इन्द्र
Indra (III) — a son of Vasiṣṭha, and Prajāpati of the <BR>Svārociṣa epoch. <BR>M. 9. 9.

इन्द्र
Indra (IV) — a division of the day. <BR>Vā. 66. 41.

इन्द्र
Indra (V) — one of Danu's sons. <BR>Vā. 68. 8.

इन्द्रकील
Indrakīla — a mountain in Bhāratavarṣa. <BR>Bhā., V. 19. 16.

इन्द्रकीलम्
Indrakīlam — a tīrtham sacred to Pitṛs. <BR>M. 22. 53.

इन्द्रकेतु
Indraketu — flags flying in the streets of Dvārakā during <BR>Kṛṣṇa's marriage with Rukmiṇi. <BR>Bhā. X. 54. 56.

इन्द्रजालम्
Indrajālam — one of the upayās of a king. <BR>M. 222. 2.

इन्द्रजित्
Indrajit (I) — a son of Rāvaṇa, killed in the Lanka war. <BR>Bhā. IX. 10. 18; Br. III. 6. 6.

इन्द्रजित्
Indrajit (II) — a son of Danu. <BR>M. 6. 19; Vā. 68. 6.

इन्द्रजित्
Indrajit (III) — a tīrtham near Garjanam on the Nar<BR>madā. <BR>M. 190. 3.

इन्द्रतापन
Indratāpana — a dānava, in the sabhā of Hiraṇyakaśipu. <BR>Br. III. 6. 8; M. 161. 81.

इन्द्रत्वम्
Indratvam — Indrahood, attained by Heti. <BR>Vā. 109. 9.

इन्द्रदत्त
Indradatta — a Kinnara with human face. <BR>Vā. 69. 35.

इन्द्रद्युम्न
Indradyumna — the son of Tejasa (Taijasa-Vā. P.). A <BR>Drāviḍa and a Pāṇḍyan king. Devoted to Hari. While <BR>engaged in tapas Agastya came to his hermitage. Finding <BR>him not extending a welcome, the angry sage cursed him to <BR>become an elephant. Indradyumna considered that to be <BR>the will of the Lord. He was born as the Lord of the ele<BR>phants, and had reminiscences of his past life;1 an account <BR>of, in the Kūrma Pūrāṇa.2 1) Bhā. VIII. 4. 7-12; Br. II. 14. 64; Vā. 33. 54; Vi. II. 1. 36.<BR> 2) M. 53. 47-8.<BR>

इन्द्रद्युम्न
Indradyumna saras — a lake through which Pāvani flows <BR>(Nalinī — Matsya P.). <BR>Br. II. 18. 56; M. 121. 55; Vā. 47. 54.

इन्द्रद्वीप
Indradvīpa — one of the nine divisions of Bhāratavarṣa:1 <BR>Here the R. Nalinī enters the sea.2 1) Br. II. 16. 9; Vā. 45. 79; Vi. II. 3. 6; M. 114. 8.<BR> 2) M. 121. 57.<BR>

इन्द्रद्वीपसमुद्र
Indradvīpasamudra — a place where Pāvanī enters the <BR>sea. <BR>Br. II. 18. 58; Vā. 47. 55.

इन्द्रधनुस्
Indradhanus — the rainbow created by Vāmadeva. <BR>M. 4. 29; Vā. 9. 52; 19. 8; Br. II. 8. 54.

इन्द्रधन्व
Indradhanva — a son of Bāṇa. <BR>Br. III. 5. 45.

इन्द्रध्वज
Indradhvaja — the fall of Cāṇūra, compared to the fall<BR>ing of. <BR>Bhā. X. 44. 23.

इन्द्रनदी
Indranadī — a R. of the Bhadra country. <BR>Vā. 43. 26.

इन्द्रपद
Indrapada — a kingdom on the west, watered by the <BR>Sindhu;1 in Gayā.2 1) Br. II. 18. 48.<BR> 2) Vā. 109. 19.<BR>

इन्द्रपालित
Indrapālita (Maurya) — the son of Bandhupālita, ruled <BR>for 10 years. <BR>Br. III. 74. 147; Vā. 99. 334.

इन्द्रप्रतिम
Indrapratima — a Vāsiṣtha and a Brahmavādin;1 a name <BR>of Kuśi, son of Vasiṣṭha.2 1) M. 145. 110.<BR> 2) Vā. 70. 88.<BR>

इन्द्रप्रमति
Indrapramat(d)i — the sage and a Vāsiṣṭha who came to <BR>see Parīkṣit practising prāyopaveśa. Learnt Ṛk Samhita <BR>from Paila and taught it to the sage Māṇḍukeya; (Markaṇ<BR>ḍeya-Vā.)1 Also known as Kuṇi;2 not to have marriage <BR>alliances with Vāsiṣṭhas and Bhagīvasu, a resident of Brah<BR>makṣetra.3 1) Bhā. I. 19. 9; XII. 6. 54-56; Br. II. 32. 115; 33. 3; 34. 25; <BR>Vā. 60. 25, 27; Vi. III. 4. 16, 19.<BR> 2) Br. III. 8. 96-7.<BR> 3) Vā. 59. 105.<BR>

इन्द्रप्रमद
Indrapramada — a sage; called on dying Bhīṣma. <BR>Bhā. I. 9. 7; 19. 9.

इन्द्रप्रस्थ
Indraprastha (t) — Yādavas of Dvāraka taken to, by <BR>Arjuna, fearing erosion of the sea. See also Hastināpuram;1 <BR>after Indra who performed penance here in honour of Parā<BR>śakti to vanquish Bhaṇḍa.2 Arjuna had Vajra crowned here.3 1) Bhā. X. 58. 1; XI. 30. 48; 31. 25.<BR> 2) Br. IV. 12. 44.<BR> 3) Vi. V. <BR>38. 34.<BR>

इन्द्रबाधनकेशि
Indrabādhanakeśi — a dānava with manuṣyadharma. <BR>Br. III. 6. 16; Vā. 68. 15.

इन्द्रबाहु
Indrabāhu — An Āgastya and Brahmiṣṭha. <BR>M. 145. 114.

इन्द्रमानसा
Indramānasā — the wife of Bāṇa and mother of Lau<BR>hitya. <BR>Vā. 67. 85.

इन्द्रमरु
Indramaru — the kingdom of. <BR>M. 121. 47.

इन्द्रयाग
Indrayāga — performed every year by Nanda and other <BR>gopas to please Indra, the Lord of rains and hence conducive <BR>to Trivarga. Kṛṣṇa explained that rain was the work of <BR>nature, and that no credit went to Indra. So he persuaded <BR>them to worship cows, Brāhmaṇas and hills. So it hap<BR>pened. Indra who was thus deprived of his bali grew wrath<BR>ful and sent down a continuous heavy downpour of rain <BR>creating panic in the minds of gopas. Kṛṣṇa took hold of <BR>the hill Govardhana and held it aloft as an umbrella steadily <BR>for seven days. Astonished at this, Indra withdrew his <BR>rains and Govardhana was planted in its place. <BR>Bhā. X. 24 (whole); ch. 25. 1-28.

इन्द्रलोकम्
Indralokam — the world of Indra. <BR>See also ‘Realm of’ under Indra (footnote 44). <BR>M. 277. 22; 278. 29; Vā. 34. 76-7; 61. 88; 111. 52.

इन्द्रवाह
Indravāha — see Puramjaya. <BR>Bhā. IX. 6. 12.

इन्द्रव्रतम्
Indravratam — of a king; to create prosperity in the <BR>country, as Indra gives rains;1 leads to the world of Indra.2 1) M. 226. 10.<BR> 2) Ib. 101. 69.<BR>

इन्द्रशत्रु
Indraśatru — one of Bhaṇḍa's councillors. <BR>Br. IV. 12. 12.

इन्द्रशैल
Indraśaila — (Mt.) a hill north of Mahābhadra lake. <BR>Vā. 36. 31.

इन्द्रसद
Indrasadas — the assembly of Indra. <BR>Vā. 2. 29.

इन्द्रसावर्णि
Indrasāvarṇi — Manu the fourteenth. Uru and others <BR>were his sons. During his period Śuci was Indra, while <BR>Agnibāhu and others were sages. Bṛhadbhānu was a mani<BR>festation of Hari. <BR>Bhā. VIII. 13. 33-35.

इन्द्रसूक्तम्
Indrasūktam — to be uttered in founding a temple. <BR>M. 265. 25.

इन्द्रसेन
Indrasena (I) — a boundary hill in Plakṣadvīpa. <BR>Bhā. V. 20. 4.

इन्द्रसेन
Indrasena (II) — a son of Devaṛṣabha. <BR>Bhā. VI. 6. 5.

इन्द्रसेन
Indrasena (III) — a son of Kūrca (Pūrva-Burnouf) and <BR>father of Vītihotra. <BR>Bhā. IX. 2. 19-20.

इन्द्रसेन
Indrasena (IV) — previously Bali. Received Kṛṣṇa and <BR>Rāma with due honours to his region Sutala, and praised <BR>their glory; gave them back their brothers killed by Kaṃsa. <BR>Bhā. X. 85. 35-46, 52.

इन्द्रसेन
Indrasena (V) — a son of Brahmiṣṭha and father of <BR>Vindhyāśva. <BR>M. 50. 6.

इन्द्रसेना
Indrasenā — the wife of Mudgola and mother of <BR>Badhyaśva. <BR>Vā. 99. 200.

