Īśa (I) — (Śiva) became Rudra through Lalita's grace.1 <BR> — also Īśāna: Image of;2 fourth mūrti as protecting Āditya.3 1) Br. IV. 6. 8, 70; 38. 40.<BR> 2) M. 261. 23.<BR> 3) M. 265. 41.<BR>

ईश
Īśa (II) — a sādhya. <BR>M. 171. 43.

