उग्रायुध
Ugrāyudha (II) — the son of Kṛta (Kārtā the Sāmaga<BR>Vā. P.) of Paurava dynasty. Father of Kṣema; slew father <BR>of Pṛthuka, the Pāñcāla Nīla: <BR>Conqueror of Nīpas: was engaged in severe austerities <BR>for 18,000 years. Was served by Janamejaya, son of Bhallāṭa. <BR>They were both attacked by Nīpas who were unmoved by <BR>Ugrāyudha's appeals for peace and protection; then Ugrā<BR>yudha asked Lord of Death to destroy them. Soon he took <BR>pity and asked Yama to save them; and this led to a scuffle <BR>between Yama and the king who got salvation. <BR>M. 49. 59-78; Vā. 99. 182, 191; Vi. IV. 19. 53-55.

