Uśanas (IV) — The preceptor of the Daityas and Asuras;1 <BR>on Śiśumāracakra;2 disciple of the father of Bṛhaspati and <BR>leader of a side of Soma (Pārṣṇi);3 father of Devayānī; by <BR>his curse Yayātī could not enjoy his youth to the full and <BR>hence requested his sons to give their youth in exchange for <BR>his old age.4 Praised Amarakaṇṭakakṣetra;5 a sage;6 see <BR>Śukra. 1) Vā. 3. 5; 62. 80; Vā. 65. 74.<BR> 2) Bhā. V. 23. 7.<BR> 3) Vā. 90. 30.<BR> 4) 65. 84; 93. 30; 103. 59.<BR> 5) Vā. 77. 14.<BR> 6) Vā. 30. 85; 59. 90.<BR>

