Kuntibhoja — (Kunti-Vā. P.), went to Syamantapañ<BR>caka for solar eclipse;1 adopted Pṛthā, daughter of Śūra, <BR>as his daughter. (See Sorenson's Index to Proper Names <BR>in Mahābhārata, p. 436). Pāṇḍu married Kuntī, daughter <BR>of Kuntibhoja.2 1) Bhā. X. 82. 25. Vi. IV. 14. 32. 3.<BR> 2) Br. III. 71. 151-2; M. <BR>46. 7; Vā. 96. 150.<BR>

