Kuntis — a Yadu tribe who took part in the marriage <BR>festivities of Kṛṣṇa and Rukminī.1 They went to Syamanta<BR>pañcaka for solar eclipse.2 Heard of Kṛṣṇa going to Mithilā <BR>and met him with presents.3 Fought with their kinsmen <BR>and ended their lives.4 1) Bhā. X. 54. 58.<BR> 2) Ib. X. 82. 13.<BR> 3) Ib. 86. 20.<BR> 4) Ib. XI. 30. 18.<BR>

