Kubera (II) — (Dhanada): the guardian of the north;1 <BR>presents of, at Umā's marriage;2 in the army of deva's at <BR>Tārakāmaya; riding animal of, man;3 Harikeśa got this status <BR>at Benares; became annada and kṣetrapāla; Udbhrama and <BR>Sambhrama, two Gaṇas in his service.4 1) M. 67. 15; Vi. V. 36. 12.<BR> 2) M. 154. 489.<BR> 3) M. 174. 17-18.<BR> 4) M. 180. 94-99.<BR>

