Kumāra (VIII) — at the commencement of the eighth <BR>kalpa Brahmā got a son (Nīlalohita) who was weeping; he <BR>asked Brahmā to give him a name for which Brahmā said <BR>Rudra; again he cried for a second name and Brahmā said, <BR>Bhava; the other names given in order were Śiva, Paśupati, <BR>Īśa, Bhīma, Ugra and Mahādeva. <BR>Vā. 27. 4-16.

कुमार
Kumāra (IX) — a Nāga. <BR>Vā. 69. 71.

