ed of Kṛṣṇa and his attitude towards <BR>them. Uddhava brought relief to them by delivering Kṛṣṇa's <BR>message while they recounted to him his deeds at Brindā<BR>van. Pleased at their attachment to the Lord, Uddhava took <BR>leave of them after spending some time there.6 They went <BR>to Syamantapañcaka and met Kṛṣṇa who took them aside <BR>and consoled them so much so that they were all in contem<BR>plation of Him. Left for Mathurā.7 and attained salvation <BR>by satsanga.8 1) Bhā. X. 21. 7-20.<BR> 2) Ib. chaps. 29-33.<BR> 3) Ib. 34. 24-32.<BR> 4) Ib. <BR>35 (whole).<BR> 5) Ib. 39. 13-32.<BR> 6) Ib. 46. 48, and ch. 47 whole.<BR> 7) Ib. <BR>82. 40-49; 84. 69.<BR> 8) Ib. XI. 12. 6; VII. 1. 30.<BR>

