Janamejaya (IV) — the son of Sṛñjaya, and father of <BR>Mahāmanas (Mahāśila-B. P.). <BR>Bhā. IX. 23. 2.

जनमेजय
Janamejaya (V) — the son of Somadatta, and father of <BR>Sumati (Prumati-Br. P.). <BR>Br. III. 61. 16; Vi. IV. 1. 57-8.

जनमेजय
Janamejaya (VI) — a son of Puramjaya and a Rājaṛṣi;1 <BR>father of Mahāśāla.2 1) M. 48. 12-3; Vā. 99. 15.<BR> 2) Vi. IV. 18. 5-6.<BR>

जनमेजय
Janamejaya (VII) — a son of Bṛhadratha, entitled Viś<BR>vajit. <BR>M. 48. 102.

जनमेजय
Janamejaya (VIII) — a son of Bhallāṭa; served Ugrā<BR>yudha in his tapas; saved Nīpas when they were led by Yama <BR>at the behest of Ugrāyudha by fighting Yama, and earned his <BR>appreciation and muktijñāna from him as a result. Wife <BR>Dhūminī and son Yavīnara. <BR>M. 49. 59-70; Vā. 99. 182.

