Janamejayas — 100 in number; according to the M. P. <BR>and Vā. P. 80 in number. <BR>Br. III. 68. 20-26; 74. 267; M. 273. 71-3; Vā. 99. 454.

जन
Jana(loka) — a divine world,1 the world of Varuṇā1a as <BR>the face of Virāṭ,2 and a part of Puruṣ.3 Its inhabitants.4 <BR>Here was in ancient times a discussion about brahmavāda, <BR>on the occasion of a sacrifice performed by Brahmā;5 at a <BR>distance of 2 crores of yojanas from Maharlokam;6 during <BR>Pralaya the Devas go from Maharloka to this.7 (See also <BR>Jana). 1) Bhā. VIII. 20. 34.<BR> 1a)Vā. 7. 28; 23. 84; 24. 3; 49. 149; 61. 129; <BR>65. 17.<BR> 2) Bhā. II. 1. 28.<BR> 3) Ib. 5. 39.<BR> 4) Ib. III. 11. 29.<BR> 5) X. 87. <BR>8-9.<BR> 6) Br. IV. I. 123; 2. 13-15, 139. Vi. II. 7. 13-14.<BR> 7) Br. I. 6. 28. <BR>Vi. VI. 3. 29.<BR>

