जनस्तम्भ
Janastambha (II) — a son of Tumba. <BR>Vā. 96. 249.

जनस्थान
Janasthāna — here Rāma vanquished a host of Rāk<BR>ṣasas;1 and performed the work of gods.2 1) Br. III. 63. 195.<BR> 2) Vā. 88. 194.<BR>

