to seek mokṣa; <BR>requested Śuka to narrate the stories of Kṛṣṇa;6 heard the <BR>whole of Bhāgavata Purāṇa from Śuka and thanked him for <BR>enlightening him on nirvāṇa;7 knew of his coming death at <BR>the hands of Takṣaka and prepared calmly to cast off his <BR>body into Gangā to attain Hari's feet; sat in contemplation <BR>in a detached spirit; bitten by Takṣaka, his body was reduc<BR>ed to ashes by the poison; universal surprise and benediction <BR>at the occurrence;8 from P. to Nanda's accession was a period <BR>of 1500 years (1050 years Vi. P.: 1015 Wilson). Father of <BR>Janamejaya and three other sons.9 1) Bhā. I. 4. 9-10; 7. 12; 12. 7-30; Br. III. 68. 21; Vā. 99. 249.<BR> 2) M. 50. 57.<BR> 3) Bhā. I. chh. 16 and 17 (whole).<BR> 4) Ib. ch. 18 whole.<BR> 5) Ib. ch. 19. 1-16, 32. 38; II. 8. 1-26; VIII. 1. 33.<BR> 6) Ib. XII. 6. 1-7.<BR> 7) Ib. II. 4. 2; XII. 6. 9-15; 12. 5-6.<BR> 8) Br. III. 74. 227, 230; M. 273. <BR>36; Vi. IV. 19. 78; 20-1.<BR> 9) Vā. 99, 229, 423; Vi. IV, 19. 78; 20. I.<BR>

