पूतना
Pūtanā (I) — a demoness and a friend of Kamsa; was <BR>deputed by him to kill all infants. Once she came to Vraja <BR>and changing her form to that of a fascinating lady, <BR>entered Nanda's house and began to suckle the baby Kṛṣṇa. <BR>He understood the purpose and sucked her life out to the <BR>wonderment of the Gopīs and Gopas. Her body was cre<BR>mated and she reached heaven;1 to be propitiated at the <BR>commencement of building operations of palaces.2 1) Bhā. X. 2. 1; 6. 2-17, 28 and 34-38; 14. 35; 26. 4; 43. 25; Br. IV. <BR>29. 124; III. 73. 100; Vā. 9. 97; 98. 100; Vi. V. 4. 1; 5. 7-11, 23; 6. <BR>23; 15. 2; 29. 5.<BR> 2) M. 268. 29.<BR>

