se;10 went with <BR>Kṛṣṇa's sacrificial horse;11 unable to recover the dead son <BR>of the Dvārakā Brahmana;12 fought with Sāmba at Prabhāsa <BR>deluded by Kṛṣṇa;13 at his death his wives burnt themselves <BR>in fire. <BR>^14 Ib. X. 31. 20; Vi. V. 33. 12; 37. 46. 1) Vi. IV. 15. 37; V. 26. 12 to the end; ch. 27 (whole); 28. 6-7; 32. <BR>1 and 6; Bhā. I. 10. 29; 11. 17; 14. 30; X. 40. 21; 61. 7 and 9; 90. <BR>35; Br. III. 71. 245; 72. 1; IV. 29. 128; Vā. 96. 237.<BR> 2) Bhā. X. ch. <BR>55 (whole); M. 47. 15, 23; 93. 51; 101; 10; 248. 48.<BR> 3) Bhā. X. 61. <BR>18, 22, 23 [8]; 90. 36. Vi. IV. 15. 39.<BR> 4) Bhā. X. 61. 26.<BR> 5) Ib. X. <BR>62. 20; Vi. V. 32. 24.<BR> 6) Bhā. X. 63. 3.<BR> 7) Ib. X. 63. 7.<BR> 8) Ib. X. <BR>64. 1-4.<BR> 9) Ib. X. 76. 13-33. 77. 1-3.<BR> 10) Ib. X. 82. 6.<BR> 11) Ib. X. 89. <BR>22. [2].<BR> 12) Ib. X. 89. 31 and 41; 90. 33.<BR> 13) Ib. XI. 30. 16.<BR>

