iding animal when it was sent to <BR>examine his mind; but still he prayed to the Lord who <BR>blessed a tīrtha at that place in his honour. 1) Bhā. III. 12. 22-23; 24. 23; IV. 1. 43; M. 3. 8; 5. 14; 9. 22; 195. <BR>8; Vi. I. 7. 5, 7, 26, 37; 8. 15.<BR> 2) M. 145. 90, 98; 171. 27; 195. 29.<BR> 3) Bhā. <BR>VII. 3. 14; VIII. 23. 20-27; XI. 27. 3; 14. 4.<BR> 4) Ib. X. 89. 2-19.<BR> 5) Ib. <BR>XII. 8. 12; IV. 14. 1; 29. 43; VI. 17. 12.<BR> 6) Ib. IV. 2. 27-8; 4. 32; 5. 17 <BR>and 19; 7. 5.<BR> 7) Ib. VI. 18. 4.<BR> 8) M. 23. 20.<BR> 9) Ib. 47. 39, 105.<BR> 10) Ib. <BR>102. 19; 126, 10; 133. 67.<BR>

