Mandākinī (I) — a R. in Bhāratavarṣa; Gangā in Deva<BR>loka;1 R. of the Kailāsa hill. Here Aila and Urvaśī lived <BR>for sometime.2 Other rivers in Kailāsa are Alakanandā and <BR>Nandā.3 1) Bhā. V. 19. 18; X. 70. 44; Vā. 45. 99.<BR> 2) Br. II. 18. 3; III. 66. <BR>6; M. 121. 4; Vā. 41. 14-17; 91. 6.<BR> 3) Ib. 41. 18; 47. 3.<BR>

