Mandākinī (II) — a R. sacred to the Pitṛs;1 rises from <BR>Ṛṣyavān;2 water for bathing a deity.3 1) M. 22. 23.<BR> 2) Ib. 105. 10; 114. 25.<BR> 3) Ib. 267. 20.<BR>

मन्दाकिन्य
Mandākinyas — Kaśyapa gotrakāras. <BR>M. 199. 3.

मन्दकूरी
Mandakūrī — a R. from the Ṛkṣa hill. <BR>Br. II. 16. 30.

मन्दार
Mandāra — a Śiva gaṇa. <BR>Br. III. 41. 27.

मन्दारवती
Mandāravatī — a division of Śrīpuram. <BR>Br. IV. 32. 33.

