Mandehas (I) — three crores of Rākṣasas who attack <BR>the rising sun and who are disarmed by the sandhya <BR>worship of gods and by the chanting of the Gāyatrī by the <BR>Brahmanas.1 1) Br. II. 21. 110; Vā. 50. 163.<BR>

मन्देह
Mandehas (II) — the Śūdra caste of Kuśadvīpa. <BR>Vi. II. 4. 38.

