Mandodaka — the lake in the Kailāsa; the water in it <BR>is like curd; the Nandana is on its bank, and the Mandākinī <BR>rises from it. <BR>M. 121. 4-5.

मन्दोदरी
Mandodarī (I) — a daughter of Maya. <BR>M. 6. 21; Vā. 68. 29.

मन्दोदरी
Mandodarī (II) — a tīrtha sacred to the Pitṛs. <BR>M. 22. 41.

मन्मथ
Manmatha — (Kāma); God of Love;1 on the third Parva <BR>of the Geyacakra;2 recreated by Lalitā, who said he was her <BR>son; went to Śiva's abode accompanied by his friend <BR>Vasanta.3 Got burnt by Śiva and in effecting his revival <BR>Māyavatī (Ratī) deluded Śambara by her charms; she <BR>brought up Pradyumna who was a part of the Love God.4 1) M. 118. 13.<BR> 2) Br. IV. 19. 67.<BR> 3) Ib. IV. 30. 46.<BR> 4) VI. V. 27. <BR>28-30.<BR>

मन्मथा
Manmathā — a goddess enshrined at Hemakūṭa. <BR>M. 13. 50.

मन्यु
Manyu (I) — a name of a Rudra. <BR>Bhā. III. 12. 12.

