Manyumān — the son of Jāṭharāgni; see Vidvānagni. <BR>Br. II. 12. 34; Vā. 29. 32.

मन्वन्तर
Manvantaras — periods of Manus; seven in number and <BR>seven to come, of Svāyambhuva, Svārociṣa, Auttama, <BR>Tāmasa, Raivata, Cākṣuṣa, Sāvarṇi (after Vaivasvata in <BR>M. P.), Raucya (Br. P.); Vaivasvata present according to the <BR>M. P.) Ruci, Bhautya, Merusāvarṇi, Rta, Ṛtadhāmān and <BR>Viṣvaksena; the last seven are future Manus;1 one of the <BR>five characteristics of the Purāṇa;2 calculation of the duration <BR>of the epochs of Manus;3 constitutes 71 yugas at the end of <BR>which comes Kṣaya4 according to Mānuṣa and Divyavat<BR>sara.5 1) Br. II. 6. 6, 20; 36. 1-4; M. 2. 22; 9. 2-36; Vā. 21. 11, 14, 19, <BR>38, 44; 57. 33-6; Vi. I. 3. 18.<BR> 2) M. 53. 65; Br. I. 1. 37; Vā. 4. 10.<BR> 3) M. 142. 30.<BR> 4) Vā. 10. 12; 32. 41.<BR> 5) Ib. 61. 138-144; 150. 176.<BR>

